The SmoothQuant Pipeline TODO List

1. Map the PyBind Signatures (The Requirements)
We need to know exactly what the C++ layer is expecting. From the fused.h and pybind.cpp files you uploaded earlier, we
have these available weapons:

    quant_per_block_int8_fuse_sub_mean_cuda(input, mean, output, scale, block_size, tensor_layout)
    mean_scale_fuse_quant_cuda(input, output, mean, scale, num_tokens, scale_max, tensor_layout)

Target: Identify which of these functions handles the Queries (Q), and which handles the Keys (K). The original code 
often uses per-warp quantization for Q and per-block for K. We need to verify if we have a sub_mean equivalent for both, 
or if we need to use mean_scale_fuse_quant_cuda as a pre-processing step.

